On the final day of this year's Spirit Week, the freshmen, sophomores and juniors decked out in white and green while the seniors wore camo. The lunch rally, held outside in the rain, included pumpkin bowling and a staff dance. Check back to The Paly Voice for more Spirit Week coverage.

&nbsp;

<iframe src="//www.youtube.com/embed/o5mpZMyNMHQ" width="560" height="315" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe>

Palo Alto High School celebrated Generations Day during Day Four of Spirit Week. The seniors dressed up as senior citizens, the juniors as sophisticates, the sophomores as teeny boppers and the freshmen as babies. The lunchtime rally included "Mannequin Painting" and "Rapid Fire." Minute to Win It competitions. During Advisory, there was a "Three Point Contest" in the Big Gym.

